queryParams.description: A comma separated list of node IDs to retrieve and convert
A number between 0.01 and 4, the image scaling factor
A string enum for the image output format, can be jpg, png, svg, or pdf

Whether text elements are rendered as outlines (vector paths) or as <text> elements in SVGs. Default: true.  Rendering text elements as outlines guarantees that the text looks exactly the same in the SVG as it does in the browser/inside Figma.  Exporting as <text> allows text to be selectable inside SVGs and generally makes the SVG easier to read. However, this relies on the browser's rendering engine which can vary between browsers and/or operating systems. As such, visual accuracy is not guaranteed as the result could look different than in Figma.
Whether to include id attributes for all SVG elements. Adds the layer name to the id attribute of an svg element. Default: false.
